	<Action id="zone1setVolume" deviceFilter="self" uiPath="Volume">
		<Name>Set Volume dB (Zone 1)</Name>
		<CallbackMethod>zone1setVolume</CallbackMethod>
		<ConfigUI>
			<Field id="volume" type="textfield" defaultValue="-30">
				<Label>Volume for Zone 1 (dB):</Label>
				<Description>Volume for Zone 1 (in dB)</Description>
			</Field>
			<Field id="label0" type="label" alignWithControl="true" fontColor="red" fontSize="small">
				<Label>BE VERY CAREFUL!</Label>
			</Field>
			<Field id="label1" type="label" alignWithControl="true" fontColor="darkgray" fontSize="small">
				<Label>Volume is expressed in terms of the full audio signal level, so a volume of 0 dB would be full volume (very loud). A moderate volume level would be around -30 dB and a quiet volume would be -50 dB.  Pioneer receivers are capabile of a volume range between -80.5 dB (no sound) and 12 dB (EXTREMELY loud). When entering a volume amount, the number must be in increments of 0.5 dB (e.g. Correct: -23.5 or -23, Incorrect: -23.9 or -23.2).
				
				
				</Label>
			</Field>
			<Field id="description" type="textfield" hidden="true">
				<Label></Label>
			</Field>
		</ConfigUI>
	</Action>
